[AFB is notifiable in the UK and known to be present in many
countries in Europe, America, and elsewhere. For the location of
Meigle, see
http://healthmap.org/r/13e1.

A detailed description with illustrations of the effects of this
bacterial disease and its diagnosis is available in chapter 2.2.2.
"American foulbrood of honey bees," OIE's Manual of Diagnostic Tests
and Vaccines for Terrestrial Animals, 2009.
http://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Health_standards/tahm/2.02.02_AMERICAN_FOULBROOD.pdf.

For additional background, see commentary in (archived) 20090804.2747. - Mod.AS]
